type.typeDefDescription: A semantic description of something, such as a concept, object, asset, technology, role or group.

summary.primitiveValue: A means of operating that makes effective use of replaceable resources.

description.primitiveValue: In the broadest sense, sustainability refers to the ability to maintain or support a process continuously over time. In business and policy contexts, sustainability seeks to prevent the depletion of natural or physical resources, so that they will remain available for the long term.

type.typeDefDescription: A link to an external reference source such as a web page, article or book.
A semantic description of something, such as a concept, object, asset, technology, role or group.

summary.primitiveValue: The Greenhouse Gas Protocol set the standards to measure and manage harmful emissions.

description.primitiveValue:
GHG Protocol establishes comprehensive global standardized frameworks to measure and manage greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from private and public sector operations, value chains and mitigation actions.

Building on a 20-year partnership between World Resources Institute (WRI) and the World Business Council for Sustainable Development (WBCSD), GHG Protocol works with governments, industry associations, NGOs, businesses and other organizations.

summary.primitiveValue: The release of a harmful substance into the atmosphere

description.primitiveValue: Human activity is causing the release of substances into the earth's atmosphere that is impacting our climate and the health of the flora and fauna that we rely on to survive.  Reducing these emissions are the focus of sustainability initiatives in order to reduce the instability in the climate and availability of resources.

type.typeDefDescription: A semantic description of something, such as a concept, object, asset, technology, role or group.

summary.primitiveValue: A type of activity that produces CO2.

description.primitiveValue: One aspect of sustainability is to reduce the amount of CO2 that is produced by the organization. The GHG protocol divides the reporting of CO2 emissions into three scopes: Scope 1, Scope 2 and Scope 3, to make it easier to monitor and build plans to reduce emissions.

summary.primitiveValue: A physical location that Coco Pharmaceuticals operates from.

description.primitiveValue: Coco Pharmaceuticals has a number of physical premises that is operates from.  Each of these premises is called a *site*

type.typeDefDescription: A semantic description of something, such as a concept, object, asset, technology, role or group.

summary.primitiveValue: The facility type captures a particular type of operation that Coco Pharmaceuticals has running at one of its sites.

description.primitiveValue: Each type of facility, such as manufacturing, research, offices, ..., needs different equipment and are likely to have different sustainability challenges.  Therefore by breaking down the activity at each site into facilities, it is possible to create a separate focus on each type of facility.

summary.primitiveValue: Graphical summary of Coco Pharmaceuticals' sustainability data.

description.primitiveValue: The sustainability dashboard provides detailed information about the impact of the different activities undertaken by Coco Pharmaceuticals' and how this mpact is changing over time.

type.typeDefDescription: Person responsible for a governance domain.

description.primitiveValue:
1) Conduct sustainability or environment-related risk assessments.
2) Create and maintain sustainability program documents, such as schedules and budgets.
3) Write project proposals, grant applications, or other documents to pursue funding for environmental initiatives.
